# awf-workflow

Use this router for every governed awf workflow. Do not load governed workflow bodies directly.

## Selection catalog

{{ if .workflowSkills }}Call `awf_workflow` alone, with no sibling tool calls, and set its `skill` argument to exactly one semantic enum value below:
{{ range .workflowSkills }}
- `{{ .Name }}`: {{ .Kind }}; {{ .Effect }}
{{ end }}
Choose by the work's semantic intent, not by a filesystem path. The tool validates lifecycle state, records the mapped effect, and returns the fixed pre-rendered body. Follow that returned body exactly.
{{ else }}No governed awf workflows are enabled. Do not call `awf_workflow` until the project enables one.
{{ end }}
Never pass a path, template text, or workflow body to `awf_workflow`. Never read `.pi/awf-workflows/` as a substitute for the tool.
